headline.main: DR. BELL, INVENTOR OF TELEPHONE, DIES; Sudden End, Due to Anemia, Comes in Seventy-Sixth Year at His Nova Scotia Home. NOTABLES PAY HIM TRIBUTE Lived to See Speech Reproduced Across the World--Pioneered in Aeronautics.

snippet: SYDNEY, N.S., Aug. 2.--Dr. Alexander Graham Bell, Inventor of the telephone, died at 2 o'clock this morning at Beinn Breagh, his estate near Baddeck.
